<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="<%= lang %>">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About - Furry Tails Photography</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
  <%- include('head-scripts') %>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include("navbar") %>

  <main>
    <!-- About Hero Section -->
    <section class="about-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="about-hero-box">
          <div class="about-hero-text">
            <h2>About</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- About Content Section -->
    <section class="about-content-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="about-content-wrapper">
          <div class="about-text-and-image">
            <div class="about-content">
              <div class="about-image">
                <img src="/gallery/me.jpg" alt="Anna, pet photographer">
              </div>
              <h3>Hi, I’m Anna, a pet photographer based in Berlin</h3>
              <p> with a big heart for animals.
My journey into pet photography began with a very personal loss. When my own beloved dog passed away, I spent hours searching through my computer for beautiful photos of her — only to realize I didn’t have nearly enough images I truly loved. I wanted to hang a few meaningful portraits on my wall, but most of the photos just didn’t feel right. The only ones that brought me real joy were a few playful shots from her birthday party against a bright pink background.
I created my in-home pet photography studio because I believe every pet deserves to be remembered with images that capture their true personality — full of life, movement, and joy.
</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about-style-box">
            <h4>My style</h4>
            <p>In my cozy homestudio in Berlin, I work with professional lighting and a variety of colourful, cheerful backgrounds. While I do take classic portraits of pets sitting, lying, or standing beautifully, my favourite moments are the ones filled with action — the zoomies, the mid-air jumps, the silly playful expressions, and all the little quirks that make your pet uniquely lovable. These energetic, fun shots are what I love capturing the most, because they show your pet's real spirit.
I photograph every session with care and patience, and I edit every single photo by hand — no filters, just thoughtful, natural editing so the final images feel warm, vibrant, and true to your pet's character.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="about-cta">
            <div class="about-cta-content">
              <div class="about-cta-text">
                <p>Ready to capture memories with your furry friend?</p>
                <a href="/<%= lang %>/contact" class="cta-button">Get in Touch</a>
              </div>
              <div class="about-cta-image">
                <img src="/gallery/gorgo.jpg" alt="Pet">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%- include('footer') %>
</body>
</html>
